cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a saliency-guided approach for complexity control in HEVC decoding, which involves modeling the relationship between decoding complexity reduction and deblocking filter disabling/motion compensation simplification, and optimizing perceptual quality. This involves techniques from multimedia (cs.MM) such as video coding and decoding, computer vision (cs.CV) such as saliency detection, information theory (cs.IT) for modeling complexity and quality loss, and neural networks (cs.NE) for optimizing quality.
